  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fourth Sector 2030 Initiative, a component of the DFID Responsible Accountable Transparent Enterprise (RATE)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A global multi-stakeholder collaboration to accelerate sustainable, inclusive growth by leveraging data, procurement, policy, and investment to scale for-benefit business models in the developing world, with a focus on strengthening the resilience and sustainability of West Africa&#x2019;s cocoa sector.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Fourth Sector 2030 Initiative aims to foster: &#x2022; At-scale market-based solutions across all the SDGs in developing countries. &#x2022; Improved livelihoods of cocoa farmers and workers while promoting environmental sustainability in West Africa&#x2019;s cocoa industry. These objectives will be accomplished through three overarching activities: (1) classification system and ecosystem mapping; (2) guidance for business, government, and investors (3) knowledge transfer and adoption.</narrative>
  </description>
